The opportunity

The Senior Business Analyst will be responsible for understanding business requirements from both IT and operational perspectives to define effective technology solutions that address business challenges. Working as part of the Business Analyst Practice team and reporting to the Team Leader, Business Analyst Practice, this role will coordinate delivery initiatives by translating them into clear, actionable, and executable requirements. The Senior Business Analyst will collaborate closely with key stakeholders to produce detailed analysis that underpins the design and measurement of future solutions. Additionally, the role will play a key part in conveying requirements across business processes, tools, and people to ensure IT gains deep insight and delivers solutions that meet operational needs while aligning with strategic objectives.

Responsibilities

Engage and build strong relationships with key Business and IT stakeholders to understand processes, identify pain points, and develop effective solutions and improvement opportunities.
Facilitate workshops and analyse current functions, processes, systems, and tools to produce clear, traceable business requirements that guide solution delivery.
Monitor and report on project and portfolio progress, proactively identifying risks and issues while recommending effective solutions and improvement opportunities.
Develop financial models and contribute to investment briefs and business cases to support analysis of current and target business states and inform strategic decision-making.
Act as the central point of knowledge for business-related queries, leading discussions and setting clear expectations for project teams.
Prepare and deliver comprehensive documentation and dry-runs to ensure a smooth go-live and seamless transition to business and IT operations teams.

Skills & Experience

Proven experience in business analysis, process management, and automation within the IT industry, including mapping, documentation, and framework development (e.g. APQC, BPMN).
Strong capability in solution design, development, and implementation, with the ability to standardise processes and templates to support consistent delivery.
Experienced in collaborating within design-led environments, applying Design Thinking and Human-Centred Design principles to drive innovation.
Excellent understanding of automation technologies, digital tools, and IT service delivery practices, supported by strong digital literacy and systems thinking.
Highly developed communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to convey complex concepts through multiple formats such as business cases and presentations.
Proficient in business analysis and project tools (e.g. MS Project, JIRA, Confluence, PowerPoint, Excel), adaptable to new technologies, and experienced in vendor and partner management.
Tertiary qualification in IT or a related discipline

About the Company
Our client is a leading organisation at the forefront of their field. With a strong commitment to innovation and operational excellence, they offer a collaborative environment where professionals are empowered to drive meaningful change. About the Position
The Process Improvement Specialist is responsible for analysing current business processes, identifying areas for enhancement, and implementing strategic initiatives to optimise organisational workflows. This role combines analytical rigor with practical implementation skills to drive measurable improvements in quality, efficiency, and cost reduction across all functional areas. You will work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to eliminate waste, streamline operations, and foster a culture of continuous improvement.
  
Must Have Skills

Analyse current business processes to identify inefficiencies, bottlenecks, and areas for improvement across production, logistics, and business operations
Develop and implement process improvement strategies using Lean Six Sigma methodologies, including DMAIC (Define, Measure, Analyse, Improve, Control) framework
Conduct comprehensive process mapping and workflow documentation to visualise current and future state processes
Perform root cause analysis to identify underlying issues and develop sustainable solutions
Gather, interpret, and analyse process data using analytics platforms to support improvement initiatives
Lead continuous improvement initiatives using Lean tools, Six Sigma principles, or Kaizen methodologies
Facilitate workshops and brainstorming sessions with stakeholders to identify opportunities and drive consensus for change
Create comprehensive process documentation including Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and work instructions
Provide training and coaching to staff on new processes and improvement methodologies
Manage end-to-end change processes within established change management frameworks to ensure successful adoption
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to implement process changes and coordinate improvement activities
Conduct cost assessments and measure company waste to eliminate inefficiencies
Benchmark processes against industry best practices and standards
Prepare comprehensive reports and presentations on process improvements and outcomes
Maintain process libraries and version control for published processes and procedures
Provide regular project status updates and reporting to management on key responsibilities and objectives
Ensure compliance with regulatory requirements, safety standards, and company policies in process designs
Identify and manage resources for process improvement projects and coordinate project timelines
  
  
Technologies and Experience

Lean Six Sigma: Experience in Yellow Belt and Above
BPMN Experience: Using and implementing the fundamentals of BPMN
Process Mapping Experience: Proven experience in developing process maps suited for executive, management, and front-line staff.
Change Management: Experience implementing the change process

Senior/Lead Business Analyst – Energy/Utilities Sector
 
We are seeking an experienced Senior/Lead Business Analyst with deep expertise in the Energy and Utilities sector to join a dynamic, forward-thinking team.

This is a hands-on leadership role, responsible for driving end-to-end project delivery across strategic reform and transformation initiatives.

In this position, you will partner closely with senior stakeholders to unpack complex business challenges, define actionable solutions, and align business needs with effective technology outcomes.

You will lead a team of Business Analysts through all phases of delivery, ensuring strategic clarity, quality, and measurable impact.

Your proven analytical and problem-solving skills will be key to delivering high-value results within tight timeframes and across diverse programs of work.
  
Key Responsibilities

Team Leadership & Guidance: Lead, coach, and provide quality oversight to a team of Business Analysts, ensuring consistency in analysis, documentation, and stakeholder engagement.
Discovery & Problem Definition: Partner with business units to identify challenges, define opportunities, and translate complex requirements into clear, actionable deliverables.
Workshop Facilitation: Design and facilitate collaborative workshops, synthesising insights into structured recommendations and solution options.
Prioritisation & Project Sizing: Oversee initiative scoping and prioritisation based on business value, feasibility, and regulatory importance.

Experience & Skills

Tertiary qualification in Business, Finance, or a related field, with 7+ years’ experience as a Senior or Lead Business Analyst.
Proven track record in the Energy, Utilities, Gas, or Electricity sector, ideally supporting regulatory reform or network transformation programs.
Skilled in business case development and executive reporting to secure investment and sponsorship.
Strong experience leading and mentoring Business Analysts in hybrid Agile/Waterfall environments.
Experience/Familiarity with SAP IS-U and enterprise-level business systems within the Energy or Utilities domain.
Advanced stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence senior leadership and regulatory bodies.
Demonstrated expertise in process mapping, current/future state analysis, and solution evaluation.
Exceptional documentation and presentation skills, including PowerPoint, Dashboards, and Roadmaps.
Experience working with collaboration tools such as MS Teams, Jira, Trello, and Confluence.

An opportunity has arisen for a Senior Business Analyst to join our Golden Grove operation in Western Australia. In this role, you will report to the Commercial Manager and work on a 4:3 roster.


Your focus will be on supporting cost and capital reporting, driving variance analysis, and partnering with the business to improve efficiency. You will be integral to embedding a culture of continuous improvement.
Your primary responsibilities will include:
Maintenance and development of internal and external cost and capital reporting, including variance analysis
Development of capital and operating budgets and forecasts

Manage the full capital life-cycle, from proposals to project close-out and depreciation.

Partner with departments to detail, document and report on business efficiency and improvement initiatives, and improve processes using the group ERP system.

About 29Metals and Golden Grove


29Metals is an ASX-listed mining company producing copper and other base and precious metals critical to the global energy transition. Headquartered in Melbourne, we also have support offices in Perth and Brisbane.


We operate two long-life assets: Golden Grove in Western Australia and Capricorn Copper in Queensland, along with a portfolio of exploration interests, including a strategic tenement package and a project in Redhill, Chile.


Golden Grove is a high-grade underground mining operation producing copper, zinc, and precious metals. With a mine life exceeding 10 years, it has strong potential for further extension. The site is currently undergoing an expansion, including the development of a new mine, the extension of existing operations, and major infrastructure upgrades.

We are seeking an experienced and highly motivated Senior Resource Equities Analyst to join our client's dedicated team on a permanent basis. This is a compelling opportunity for a professional with a deep understanding of the resource sector to contribute to investment strategies and analysis.

• Located in vibrant Sydney or Melbourne CBD. If you possess the required skills and experience and are looking for a challenging yet rewarding opportunity, we encourage you to apply

Summary:

Forget what you know about typical analyst roles. This isn't about building decks that disappear into committees or running models that never see daylight. This is about sitting at the table where decisions get made, capital gets deployed, and businesses get built.

The Castle Steering Group is the agile innovation engine behind a dynamic multi-entity portfolio spanning hospitality, property, technology, and energy. Its the team that identifies what's next, pressure-tests what matters, and drives momentum across existing businesses while hunting for the opportunities that will define our future.

We're looking for an exceptional Research Analyst—a high-achiever with 5-7 years of battle-tested experience who's ready to move from advising on deals to being inside them. If you've been waiting for a role where your analysis directly influences investment decisions and your recommendations shape strategy, this is it.

What You'll Actually Do

Investment Research & Deal Flow - You'll actively research and evaluate new investment opportunities across sectors, conducting rigorous market analysis, competitive positioning, and commercial due diligence. You'll build the business cases that inform go/no-go decisions on new ventures and acquisitions

Strategic Due Diligence - Execute detailed investigations into potential investments—financial modeling, cross-comparisons against market leaders, risk assessment, and operational feasibility. Your work will directly inform capital allocation decisions, not sit in a filing cabinet.

Portfolio Momentum Management - Keep existing businesses focused and moving forward. You'll identify operational bottlenecks, research efficiency improvements, analyze performance metrics, and recommend actions that unlock growth across the portfolio.

Board-Ready Analysis - Prepare investment memoranda, business cases, and strategic briefing materials for the Group CEO and Castle Steering Group. Your analysis needs to be sharp, defensible, and decision-ready—no fluff, just insight.

Cross-Functional Intelligence - Work alongside the Strategic Advisor on high-level strategy, collaborate with the Investment Manager on deal structuring, and coordinate with the CEO's EA to ensure seamless execution of research deliverables and presentations.

Market Intelligence & Trends - Maintain ongoing sector surveillance across hospitality, property, technology, and energy. Identify emerging opportunities, competitive threats, and market shifts before they become obvious. Be the person who sees what's coming.

Who We're Looking For

5-7 years in investment banking, management consulting, or corporate strategy
Direct experience in deal analysis, due diligence, or investment evaluation
Demonstrated ability to build robust financial models and business cases
Track record of influencing senior stakeholders with analytical insights
Excellent written and verbal communication—you can distill complexity into clarity

The Differentiators

High-Achiever Mentality

You're the person who consistently exceeds expectations and raises the bar
Track record of being the "go-to" analyst on your team
Intellectually curious—you dig deeper than required because you genuinely want to understand
Comfortable with ambiguity and able to structure unstructured problems

Agile Operator

You thrive in fast-moving environments where priorities shift and speed matters
Comfortable working across multiple projects simultaneously without losing quality
Don't need hand-holding—you identify what needs to be done and do it
Resilient under pressure and energized by intensity rather than overwhelmed by it

Commercial Instinct

You understand that analysis exists to drive decisions, not to be academically interesting
Can balance thoroughness with pragmatism—knowing when 80% certainty is enough to move
Sharp commercial awareness across multiple sectors
Think like an investor, not just an analyst

Team Player with Presence

Confident presenting to and engaging with the Group CEO and senior leadership
Collaborative approach when working with Strategic Advisor, Investment Manager, and EA
Professional demeanor with discretion around sensitive commercial information
Humble enough to learn, confident enough to challenge assumptions constructively

What Success Looks Like

You'll know you're succeeding when:

Ad Text:
Senior Business Analyst (Multilateral Batches - ISO 20022 Migration)

Payments Settlements Department

Contribute to the future of Australia's payments infrastructure
Collaborate on a high-impact transformation project
Fixed-term contract until November 2026 in a hybrid working environment


Do work that makes a difference

Join the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) and contribute to the strategic transformation of Australia's payments settlements infrastructure. As part of the Multilateral Batches- ISO Migration project, we are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to support the critical business analysis activities.

This is a unique opportunity to work on a high-profile initiative that helps evolving settlement service. You will play a key role in guiding the adoption of ISO 20022 messaging standards for multilateral batches, ensuring alignment with industry-wide developments and compliance requirements.

Working within the Payments Settlements Department, you'll collaborate with multidisciplinary teams and external stakeholders to deliver secure, stable, and efficient payment solutions that support the Australian financial system.


About the role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you will:

Collaborate with stakeholders to elicit, analyse, and document business and technical requirements.
Contribute to the development of project plans, contractual arrangements, user guides, procedures and other documentation as required.
Act as a liaison between business units and IT teams to align solutions with business goals.
Support project administrative activities such as preparing meeting minutes, updating status reports and monitoring and reporting project issues, risks and assumptions.
Collaboratively work with internal and external stakeholders and assist in developing industry integration and migration approach.
Ensure adherence to regulatory and information management standards.
As required, participate in industry consultations and provide analysis of related documentation.
Actively contribute to knowledge sharing and continuous improvement within and across teams.


About you

You will bring:

Proven experience as a Senior Business Analyst in complex, multi-stakeholder environments-ideally within payments or financial services programs.
Experience working on system integration, messaging, or compliance-related projects.
Advanced skills in requirements elicitation, documentation, and stakeholder engagement.
Ability to work independently and manage competing priorities in a fast-paced environment.
Experience in developing and maintaining project documentation (e.g.: Project Plan, Status Reports).
Proficiency in JIRA and Confluence for managing requirements and documentation.
A collaborative mindset with the ability to build strong relationships and support the needs of diverse stakeholders.
Leadership and mentoring experience within the BA community to support the growth of BA practice.
Demonstrated ability to manage end-to-end business analysis activities and deliverables independently.
Strong understanding of ISO 20022 messaging standards and their application in payment systems. (Highly Desirable)
Tertiary qualifications in Business, Economics, Information Technology or Computer Science.
Project Management or Business Analysis qualifications/accreditations.


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Ad Text:
ASIS is Australia’s overseas secret intelligence collection agency. Its mission is to protect and promote Australia’s vital interests through the provision of intelligence services as directed by the Australian Government. Its work can involve collecting intelligence relating to national security, international relations and economic issues. It also contributes to Australia’s coordinated national efforts against terrorism, proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, and trans-national issues such as people smuggling. 

ASIS employs people in a wide range of roles, including technologists. These roles require dynamic team players who enjoy working with stakeholders, team members and individually on projects. ASIS is looking for people who will be able to meet tight deadlines and work to support ASIS priorities. Successful candidates will have excellent coordination and administration skills, excellent verbal and written communication skills; and, strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills. Relevant tertiary qualifications and demonstrable experience will be highly regarded. 

ASIS is a diverse and inclusive workplace, where our people are empowered through authenticity and a sense of belonging to achieve their potential and contribute to a shared purpose and mission. We seek to reflect the community we serve, and welcome applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, women, people with a disability, neurodiverse, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and those who identify as LGBTIQA+. 

We offer a competitive salary package including 22 days annual leave, shutdown between Christmas and New Years Day, 15.4% employer superannuation contribution, and generous paid parental leave. Full and part time positions as well as flexible work hours can be negotiated.

All positions are office-based and located in Canberra. This role requires the successful applicant to obtain and maintain a Security Clearance.

 

Role: Director of Data Science (Executive Level 2)

We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Director of Data Science to lead our data science team. In this role, you will be responsible for driving the strategic direction of data science within ASIS, ensuring that our data capabilities support and enhance our intelligence mission. You will work closely with stakeholders across the organisation to identify opportunities for data-driven insights and operational impact. ASIS is at the forefront of intelligence capability and rapidly adopts the latest in technology to deliver novel solutions to real-world problems. A genuinely agile approach combined with strong governance has made ASIS a leader in the adoption and development of Artificial Intelligence. It is the responsibility of the Director of Data Science to ensure that capability development and adoption keeps pace with the demands of operations and that ASIS maintains its leadership position. 

Key Responsibilities and Tasks:

·        Develop and implement the data science strategy in alignment with ASIS’s mission and priorities.

·        Lead and grow a team of data scientists, providing technical guidance, mentoring, and performance management.

·        Collaborate with intelligence analysts, technologists, and other stakeholders to identify and address data science needs.

·        Oversee the deployment, training, and re-training of the latest machine learning models.

·        Ensure the ethical and secure use of data, adhering to relevant laws, regulations, and ASIS policies.

·        Stay abreast of advancements in data science and technology, and evaluate their potential application within ASIS.

·        Represent ASIS in external forums and collaborations related to data science and intelligence.

Core Skills / Education, qualification and experience requirements

Proven experience in a senior data science role, with a strong track record of leading data science teams and projects.
Advanced degree in data science, computer science, mathematics, statistics, or a related field.
Extensive experience in data analysis, machine learning, and statistical modelling.
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, Scala/Spark, or C++.
Strong leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.
Demonstrated ability to translate complex technical concepts into actionable insights for non-technical stakeholders.
Experience in working with large, complex datasets, including structured and unstructured data.
Knowledge of open-source data science tools and technologies, such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, and Apache Spark.
Preferably, an understanding of the intelligence cycle and the role of data science in supporting intelligence operations.

Experience in the following would be beneficial, but not essential:

·        Demonstrated Knowledge of the Intelligence Services Act 2001.

·        Previous experience in the National Intelligence Community.

Role: Data Manager (EL1)

We are seeking a skilled and motivated Data Manager to ensure our data is managed effectively, securely, and in compliance with legal and privacy obligations. You will maintain the reliability and trustworthiness of our data through data quality management processes including monitoring and validation.

Your expertise will be essential for exploring data, uncovering insights to inform decision-making. You will also promote data literacy and foster a data-driven culture by educating users on data concepts and tools. 

Strong collaboration and communication skills are vital for working with diverse stakeholders and clearly conveying complex data concepts. You will contribute to planning and coordinating work, and build a strong team culture to enhance efficiency and effectiveness. 

Key Responsibilities and Tasks

The following is an overview of key responsibilities and tasks:

·        Lead a team of Data specialists.

·        Oversee the management and curation of data in accordance with existing compliance frameworks and specifications to enable its use in ASIS data tools and systems, supporting it’s activities.

·        Provide expert support and advice to business partners on data management matters.

·        Engage collaboratively with internal and external stakeholders, promoting effective communication and driving positive team results.  

·        Contribute to data governance initiatives, adhere to established policies and maintain data quality and integrity.

·        Develop bespoke training courses and presentations on data management and use. 

·        Clearly and effectively communicate complex data concepts and issues to non-specialist users.

·        Identify and implement the strategic goals of the agency as they apply to data management.

Core Skills

The following is an overview of skills required to succeed in the role:

·        Interest in data and its application: Passionate about leveraging data to drive insights and inform business decisions.

·        Critical thinking: Able to interpret complex data, identify trends, and solve problems through logical reasoning.

·        Technical skills: Proficient in using tools and technologies to manage, analyse, and visualize data effectively.

·        Attention to detail: Meticulous in ensuring data accuracy, consistency, and quality through careful review and organisation.

·        Curiosity and inquisitiveness: Driven by a desire to explore data, ask insightful questions, and uncover hidden patterns and trends.

·        Communication skills: Clearly and effectively conveys complex data findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders, fostering collaboration and understanding.

Education, qualification and experience requirements

The following education, qualifications and/or experience will be highly regarded:

·        Experience in one or more of the following areas, library and information services, data quality, data stewardship or data management practice would be highly regarded but not essential.

·        Experience or ability to apply data management principles within the scope of relevant legislative and/or governance frameworks.

·        Experience in championing data literacy would be highly regarded by not essential.

·        Technical skills that assist in data manipulation would be highly regarded but not essential.

We are dedicated to building a diverse and inclusive workforce, so if you are excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply.

Data Engineer - Commercial Risk Analytics

An exciting opportunity has become available for a passionate and innovative professional to join our dynamic Commercial Risk Analytics Team. In this role, you will be transforming data into actionable insights that drive business success, while ensuring the detailed integration of cutting-edge technology and strategic analytics.

This is a hybrid role with the flexibility to work both virtually and from our Aon offices.

Aon is in the business of better decisions

At Aon, we shape decisions for the better to protect and enrich the lives of people around the world.

As an organization, we are united through trust as one inclusive, diverse team, and we are passionate about helping our colleagues and clients succeed.

What the day will look like

Data Assets Design: Develop and enhance data assets tailored to business needs, supporting analytics and intelligence projects.
Automated Pipelines: Create and lead automated data ingestion pipelines using Databricks with AWS S3, and SSIS with Microsoft Azure.
Data Quality: Implement routines for data cleaning and standardization, using Python in Databricks notebooks for quality assurance.
SQL Development: Craft SQL scripts for data views, optimizing data flows to introduce new report dimensions and metrics.
Deployment & Monitoring: Deploy notebooks and scripts in production, configure cloud auto-scaling, and supervise performance. Integrate API solutions for GenAI module triggers.
Troubleshooting: Address data ingestion and processing issues, ensuring smooth report generation in PowerBI.
Collaboration: Work closely with data scientists, domain experts, and commercial risk leaders to build data infrastructure to support a broad variety of client risk analytics and business intelligence projects.
Technical Translation: Convert business requirements into technical specifications.

How this opportunity is different

As an Aon colleague, you will never be limited by your job title. Instead, you will learn and grow alongside some of the most versatile individuals in the business, who genuinely want you to be the best version of yourself.

We honestly believe that our culture is different, with authentic and inquisitive individuals who each bring something unique to our team.

Skills and experience that will lead to success

This role seeks for a forward-thinking Data Engineer to support our growing Commercial Risk Analytics team. Additionally, you will have the following:

5+ years of experience in data engineering, analytics, or business intelligence
Proficiency in SQL, Python, and cloud-based ETL tools like SSIS or Alteryx
Hands-on experience with Databricks (or similar platforms)
Knowledge of data architectures (data warehouses, lakehouse, and data mesh)
Skilled in Power BI for visualization and dashboard troubleshooting
Ability to document workflows, conduct testing, and ensure data quality
Experience integrating APIs and GenAI modules is a plus
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, or a related field (Master’s a plus)

Preferred

Databricks certification
Exposure to MLOps and Natural Language Processing (NLP)

 

How we support our colleagues

In addition to our comprehensive benefits package, we encourage a diverse workforce. Plus, our agile, inclusive environment allows you to manage your wellbeing and work/life balance, ensuring you can be your best self at Aon. Furthermore, all colleagues enjoy two “Global Wellbeing Days” each year, encouraging you to take time to focus on yourself. We offer a variety of working style solutions, but we also recognise that flexibility goes beyond just the place of work... and we are all for it. We call this Smart Working!

Our continuous learning culture inspires and equips you to learn, share and grow, helping you achieve your fullest potential. As a result, at Aon, you are more connected, more relevant, and more valued.
